Here's a thing. A few months ago I got a call out of the blue from a researcher who said that Bob Lazar, yes the alien bodies Area 51 dude, had told people that he’d done camera work on Blondie videos. No further info just that and could I verify. 
I have no way of knowing and I told the guy to try and reach out to various directors. Amazing really. Lazar has been trending mightily the last few weeks w all the UAP stuff going on.
Hey Bob @unitednuclearbob if you see this what’s the story?

Later
I wrote to Bob's site and they actually wrote back saying there was nothing to this. They went so far as to suggest that people used this kind of story to discredit Bob, I guess to dilute his claims with a lot of extra fringe events that he wasn't a part of

We lost our daughter and sister Akira at the end of May to an overdose. I've been posting as usual because it distracts from the heartbreak. 
There are a lot of you I care for that didn't know and even though it's not like me to post personal events publicy Akira was important to many. She was wonderful and a bright place in the world. She had been struggling for years and addiction took her.
Barbara Vali and I are moving ahead but there's a huge piece missing from our lives.
Just remember her and be kind to each other and you young people please avoid this trap.
♥️

Awesome old newspaper piece about the location of CBGBs that was in 1878 or so a 'wholesale liquor store'

BURGLAR OR AN ASTRAL BODY
Eight Bowery Policemen Surround Something with a Cup in Its Hair, but the Something Proves Nothing.

Some one who knows all about astral bodies might explain about a mysterious burglar, or the astral body of a burglar, that threw the Bowery into a state of excitement yesterday morning. before daylight.
Eight policemen surrounded the burglar and closed in on him, only to find that he had vanished.
The Bowery had gone to sleep when Policeman Timothy Keyes saw a shadow on the window of the wholesale liquor store 315 Bowery.
He went on tiptoe to the window and looked in.
A dim light came from a gas burner turned low. He could see he says, a seven-year-old boy, with a big
shock of hair, reaching up and turningig the combination of the safe.The policeman said
that in the centre of the shock 
of hair was a little round
cup, and that the boy wore a striped shirt and brown trousers.Keyes called for help. Eight policemen came.
"Whist!" Said policeman Keyes; "If we are careful we will capture a burglar. He is at work. I saw him."
Then the policemen surrounded the store and guarded every means of exit from the celler to the roof.
They finally broke in the door with an axe and searched the place.
Henry Steinhardt, one of the owners of the store, arrived just then accompanied by two salesmen. He had been summoned from his home, 312 West One Hundred and
Fifteenth Street, by a Police Sergeant, who told him a burglar was in his store.
There was a large crowd of persons waiting on the street when the policemen and Steinhardt searched
the store. They looked everywhere but they found no boy of any description nor could Mr Steinhardt
when daylight came, find any trace of a burglar.

Here we go. I've been working on this memoir for two years and it'll show up allegedly in 2024.

After breaking our necks touring for all of 1977, Blondie wound up at a little run down resort on Great Keppel Island which is off the coast of Queensland Australia. I set up this Roland gear and sat around smoking hash and jamming and making cassettes. It was balmy and charming.
We played a few sets for the handful of tourists on the island. This was Dec 77. 
While we were doing a show some guys broke into all the rooms and stole shit. They did get caught by the local cops but I didn't get the hash back
